Many people talk about their university experiences as if they were life-changing. Many meet their partners in higher education. Others find their calling in life. A certain percentage get wasted every weekend and look back on those times fondly. But for me, the city is the well-spring of life. For a well-off white guy from the suburbs, living in a city has been illuminating. Nowhere are the divides starker. Brand-new luxury apartments jut  out of the ground in East Liberty, a black, working-class neighborhood that is becoming increasingly populated by well-off white tech workers. Larimer just next door 
